  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard Twin Rooms</strong> measure 16m² and sleep two to three people (extra bed is a single sofa bed). They have a bath or a shower with a step.</p>
<p><strong>Standard Balcony Rooms </strong>are 16m² and sleep two to three people (extra bed is a single sofa bed). They have a balcony and a shower stall with a step.</p>
<p><strong>Privilege Twin Rooms</strong> are 16m² and sleep two people. They have a modern style with a flat screen TV, balcony and shower stall with a step. There are also free soft drinks in the minibar and come with some sparkling wine.</p>
<p><strong>Standard Twin Rooms for sole use</strong> are also available. They have a bath with showerhead.</p>
<p>Please request twin or double beds at the time of booking.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Air-conditioning (mid-June to mid-September)</li>
<li>Tea &amp; coffee making facilities</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Minibar</li>
<li>Safe</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees &amp; taxes</strong></p>
<p>A tourist tax of approx. €1.50 per person per day is payable locally.</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
